  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (d4c615b 2022-03-24T01:05:20.744764+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kalidao/multi-sig/actions/runs/2031799602\r\n\r\nThis pipeline passed against the version of forge from 3 nights ago, when re-run against the present version there is an error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  arithmetic operation overflow\r\nLocation: /home/runner/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/primitive-types-0.11.1/src/lib.rs:38\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n/home/runner/work/_temp/618a42db-63b4-4979-9c12-59756dd77729.sh: line 1:  2851 Aborted                 (core dumped) forge test --optimize\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis can be verified and debugged against that commit, or the present main branch of the kali-dao repo. I haven't been able to pin down where the regression was introduced, but it looks like it was in the last nightly.",
